question:
What is the output of the following code?

public class Test {
    public static void modify(int x, StringBuilder sb) {
        x = 10;
        sb.append(" World");
    }
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int a = 5;
        StringBuilder builder = new StringBuilder("Hello");
        modify(a, builder);
        System.out.println(a + " " + builder);
    }
}

What is the result of attempting to change the reference inside a method?

public class Test {
    static void changeReference(String str) {
        str = "Changed";
    }
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String s = "Original";
        changeReference(s);
        System.out.println(s);
    }
}
